  ],
  "text": "Firefox's multi-process (Fission) architecture manages content processes through several key components in dom/ipc/:\n\n1. **ContentParent** (dom/ipc/ContentParent.h and dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp): The parent-side content process manager. ContentParent is defined at line 118 of ContentParent.h as 'class ContentParent final' and extends PContentParent, nsIDOMProcessParent, and other interfaces. It manages the lifecycle and communication of a single content process.\n\n2. **ContentProcessManager** (dom/ipc/ContentProcessManager.h and dom/ipc/ContentProcessManager.cpp): The global registry of all active content processes. ContentProcessManager is defined at line 19 of ContentProcessManager.h as 'class ContentProcessManager final' and provides methods like AddContentProcess(), RemoveContentProcess(), and GetContentProcessById() to maintain a mapping of content process IDs to ContentParent instances.\n\n3. **BrowserParent** (dom/ipc/BrowserParent.h): The parent-side representation of a remote tab/browser. BrowserParent is defined at line 84 of BrowserParent.h as 'class BrowserParent final' and extends PBrowserParent and TabContext. Each BrowserParent is associated with a ContentParent and manages tab-specific IPC communication.\n\n4. **PreallocatedProcessManager** (dom/ipc/PreallocatedProcessManager.h and dom/ipc/PreallocatedProcessManager.cpp): Manages a pool of pre-allocated content processes for faster process creation. PreallocatedProcessManager is defined at line 31 of PreallocatedProcessManager.h as 'class PreallocatedProcessManager final' and provides methods like AddBlocker(), RemoveBlocker(), and Take() to manage the lifecycle of preallocated processes.\n\nAll these files are located in the dom/ipc/ directory under github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8 and work together to implement Firefox's content process lifecycle management."
}

